Perion Network - Wikipedia





















 






Perion Network

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search


Perion Network Ltd.





Type

Public


Traded as
NASDAQ: PERI, TASE: PERI


Industry
Ad-tech, Internet


Founder
Yaron Adler, Ofer Adler


Headquarters
Holon, Israel



Area served

Worldwide



Key people

Doron Gerstel (CEO)
Ophir Yakovian (CFO)[1]
Mike Glover (GM)[2]


Products
CodeFuel, Undertone, MakeMeReach, Smilebox, Incredimail


Revenue
 US$330.75 million (2014)



Operating income

 US$55.29 million (2014)



Net income

 US$42.82 million (2014)



Number of employees

400 (as of April 30, 2015)


Website
perion.com


Perion is an Israel-based ad-tech company providing engagement and monetization solutions for web and mobile based digital businesses.[3] Their headquarters are in Holon, Israel, with offices in San Francisco, New York City, Boston, Chicago, Washington DC, Los Angeles, Atlanta, Milan, Hamburg, Düsseldorf, Paris and Barcelona.[4][5]



Contents


1 History
2 Products
3 See also
4 References



History[edit]
Perion was formerly IncrediMail, an email company founded in 1999 by cousins Yaron and Ofer Adler.[6] Soon after its founding, they raised $3.3 million from private and institutional sources and IPOed on NASDAQ in January 2006. They listed on the Tel Aviv Stock Exchange in 2007.[7]
Perion was managed by its original founders until August 2010, when Josef Mandelbaum was appointed CEO.[8] Mandelbaum had previously been CEO of American Greetings Interactive, the internet branch of American Greetings. In August 2011 Perion acquired the Redmond-based Smilebox for $32 million. Smilebox is an application for creating slideshows and other digital photo albums.[9][10]
In November 2011 they changed the company name to Perion, the Hebrew word for productivity. In November 2012 Perion purchased Israel-based SweetPacks (aka SweetIM) for approximately $41 million.[11][12] SweetPacks produced a variety of downloadable content for everyday use. In January 2014, they acquired Conduit’s ClientConnect business in an all-stock transaction valued at $660 million.[13]
In June 2014, Perion acquired San Francisco based GrowMobile.[14] In February 2015, Perion acquired Paris-based MakeMeReach - a social media advertising platform.[15] After their move to Holon, Perion Network incorporated CSR policies into their corporate strategy. 2% of its net profits is donated and all employees are permitted to spend up to 40 hours per year volunteering in the community.[16]
In December 2015, Perion acquired the digital advertising company Undertone for $180 million.[17][18] In January 2017, Perion announced the appointment of new CEO Doron Gerstel, effective April 2017, followed by the announcement of Josef Mandelbaum stepping down from the company.[19] Later in the year, the company's unit MakeMeReach was named as a Snapchat Partner.[20]
Products[edit]
Undertone helps brands engage consumers through cross-screen and digital ad experiences. CodeFuel allows developers to generate revenue using search syndication.[5] MakeMeReach is a social media marketing tool to help advertisers grow demand for their brand on Facebook, Twitter, Instagram & Snapchat. The mobile and desktop apps are IncrediMail, an email program and Smilebox, a desktop and mobile app for customizing and animating photos.[21]
See also[edit]

